===Etymology===
{{ja-kanjitab|おぎ|yomi=kun}}
From {{inh|ja|ojp|-}}. Found in the ''{{w|Man'yōshū}}'', completed some time after 759 {{CE}}.<ref name="MYS">{{RQ:Manyoshu|14|3446}}, text [https://web.archive.org/web/20200925204109/http://jti.lib.virginia.edu/japanese/manyoshu/Man14Yo.html#3446 here]</ref>

Ultimate derivation {{unc|ja|nocap=1}}. One theory suggests that it might be the {{m|ja|連用形|tr=ren'yōkei||continuative or stem form}} of classical verb {{m|ja|招く|tr={{upright|ancient reading}} woku, {{upright|modern rendering}} oku||to invite, to beckon someone closer|pos=also found in some texts with the ancient reading ''wogu''}}, from the way the grass waves in the wind.<ref>{{R:Nihon Jiten|オギ・荻|46206}}</ref>

